Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Cut the @cauliflower{1} into florets (like small trees), halving any larger ones.
Pop them onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer, then sprinkle over
half the @white cumin seeds{1/2%tsp}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{15-18%mins}.
Turn halfway through.

While the cauli roasts, pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a
#lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the
@flaked almonds{15%g} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted,
~{3-4%mins}.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Transfer the almonds to a small #bowl{} and pop your pan back on medium high heat.

Add a drizzle of oil, the @tikka masala paste{75%g}, garlic and remaining
@white cumin seeds{1/2%tsp} to the pan. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%secs}.

Pour the @tomato passata{1}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and
@water{100%ml}(for the curry) into the pan.

Stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g}.

Bring to the boil, then turn the heat down slightly. Simmer until thickened,
~{4-5%mins}, stirring occasionally.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir through the @peas{120%g}, @red pepper chilli
jelly{1} and @butter{20%g}.

Once cooked, gently stir the roasted cauliflower through the sauce.

Cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}, then remove the pan from the heat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

When everything is ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between
your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the cauliflower and pea tikka masala.

Scatter with the toasted flaked almonds to finish. Enjoy!